Wait, wait, wait.

161
00:08:36,429 --> 00:08:37,110
Young Lord.

162
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:38,990
Why does the Dragon Capital's

163
00:08:38,990 --> 00:08:40,409
curse-breaking spell

164
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:43,200
sound like some kind of rural ritual?

165
00:08:43,950 --> 00:08:45,780
What do you mean?

166
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,810
Forget it.

167
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:49,510
Thank you.

168
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:50,910
I'll figure it out myself.

169
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:51,590
No, no, no.

170
00:08:52,410 --> 00:08:53,640
I have another idea.

171
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:55,800
I promise that it's effective.

172
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:57,550
There's another way?

173
00:08:58,750 --> 00:08:59,720
Could it be...

174
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,010
Using a black dog's blood?

175
00:09:03,590 --> 00:09:04,640
How did you know?

176
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:06,930
All right.

177
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,660
Pretend I didn't ask you anything

178
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:10,750
about breaking curses or exorcising evil.

179
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:11,810
You must not mention this

180
00:09:11,810 --> 00:09:12,730
to anyone.

181
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,350
Understand?

182
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,470
